---
// Market.astro — DS-07
---

<section id="market" class="relative bg-navy">
  <div class="rule-cyan"></div>

  <div class="max-w-content mx-auto px-6 md:px-12 py-20 md:py-[120px]">

    <!-- Header -->
    <div class="reveal mb-20">
      <p class="font-mono font-semibold text-[18px] text-cyan uppercase tracking-[0.2em] mb-4">THE MARKET</p>
      <h2 class="font-grotesk font-bold text-off-white mb-5" style="font-size: clamp(34px, 5vw, 52px); letter-spacing: -0.02em; max-width: 700px;">
        A growing market. An untouched inventory category.
      </h2>
      <p class="font-grotesk text-mid-grey text-lg" style="max-width: 640px; line-height: 1.65;">
        Digital Out-of-Home is one of the fastest-growing channels in advertising. The infrastructure to monetise it at scale already exists. Construction scaffolding &mdash; one of the most prominent and widely distributed structures in every UK city &mdash; has never been part of it. Until now.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Section image -->
    <div class="reveal mb-16 -mx-6 md:-mx-12 overflow-hidden rounded-md mx-0">
      <img
        src="/market-dusk.jpeg"
        alt="DigiSite screens illuminating a UK city street at dusk with pedestrians and traffic"
        width="1536"
        height="1024"
        loading="lazy"
        class="w-full h-[240px] md:h-[360px] object-cover"
      />
    </div>

    <!-- 2x2 stat grid -->
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-[2px] mb-16 reveal-stagger">

      <!-- Stat 1 -->
      <div class="reveal bg-section border border-cyan/10 p-10 md:p-12 rounded-md">
        <span class="font-mono font-semibold text-5xl md:text-7xl text-cyan leading-none" style="letter-spacing: -0.02em;" data-counter data-target="20" data-prefix="$" data-suffix=".7bn">0</span>
        <p class="font-mono font-semibold text-[13px] uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-mid-grey mt-3">GLOBAL DOOH MARKET 2024</p>
        <p class="font-grotesk text-[15px] text-mid-grey mt-4" style="line-height: 1.65;">
          Growing at 10.7% annually &mdash; one of the fastest-growing channels in advertising globally. Programmatic DOOH is accelerating this growth further as brands shift budgets from digital display into physical environments.
        </p>
        <p class="font-mono text-[10px] text-mid-grey/55 mt-4">Statista / OAAA, 2024</p>
      </div>

      <!-- Stat 2 -->
      <div class="reveal bg-section border border-cyan/10 p-10 md:p-12 rounded-md">
        <span class="font-mono font-semibold text-5xl md:text-7xl text-cyan leading-none" style="letter-spacing: -0.02em;" data-counter data-target="83" data-suffix="%">0</span>
        <p class="font-mono font-semibold text-[13px] uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-mid-grey mt-3">OF UK POPULATION REACHED WEEKLY</p>
        <p class="font-grotesk text-[15px] text-mid-grey mt-4" style="line-height: 1.65;">
          Digital OOH screens reach 83% of the UK population every week, according to Route &mdash; the UK's Joint Industry Currency for outdoor audience measurement. DigiSite inventory is measured by the same standard as every major billboard network in the country.
        </p>
        <p class="font-mono text-[10px] text-mid-grey/55 mt-4">Route / Outsmart, 2024</p>
      </div>

      <!-- Stat 3 -->
      <div class="reveal bg-section border border-cyan/10 p-10 md:p-12 rounded-md">
        <span class="font-mono font-semibold text-5xl md:text-7xl text-amber leading-none" style="letter-spacing: -0.02em;">4&times;</span>
        <p class="font-mono font-semibold text-[13px] uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-mid-grey mt-3">REVENUE UPLIFT: STATIC TO DIGITAL</p>
        <p class="font-grotesk text-[15px] text-mid-grey mt-4" style="line-height: 1.65;">
          Converting a static advertising location to digital typically generates four times the annual revenue from the same site. DigiSite is applying this proven formula to a location type &mdash; construction scaffolding &mdash; that currently generates zero.
        </p>
        <p class="font-mono text-[10px] text-mid-grey/55 mt-4">Outsmart / industry benchmarks</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Competitor landscape -->
    <div class="reveal bg-cyan/[0.03] border-t border-b border-cyan/10 py-12 -mx-6 md:-mx-12 px-6 md:px-12 mb-16">
      <div class="max-w-content mx-auto grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-[30%_70%] gap-8">
        <div>
          <p class="font-mono font-semibold text-[13px] uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-cyan">COMPETITIVE POSITION</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-grotesk font-bold text-[22px] text-off-white mb-4">
            DigiSite operates in a niche with no direct UK competition.
          </h3>
          <p class="font-grotesk text-[16px] text-mid-grey" style="line-height: 1.7;">
            Existing scaffold advertisers in the UK use printed static wraps and banners &mdash; not digital screens. The companies selling static scaffold advertising are not competitors; they are the baseline DigiSite replaces. The closest international comparable is Doka's SiteLight system in Germany. In the UK, there is no established operator deploying digital LED screens on construction scaffolding at scale. DigiSite enters this market as a first-mover with a clearly defined operational model, proven hardware, and an established regulatory pathway.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Oxford Street precedent -->
    <div class="reveal bg-section border border-amber/20 rounded-md p-8 md:p-12 mb-16">
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-[60%_40%] gap-8 items-center">
        <div>
          <p class="font-mono font-semibold text-[13px] uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-amber mb-4">LEGAL PRECEDENT</p>
          <h3 class="font-grotesk font-bold text-[22px] text-off-white mb-4" style="letter-spacing: -0.01em;">
            Oxford Street, London. 2024. The first digital screen on UK construction scaffolding.
          </h3>
          <p class="font-grotesk text-[15px] text-mid-grey" style="line-height: 1.7;">
            In 2024, the first digital LED screen on construction scaffolding was approved and installed on Oxford Street &mdash; the UK's most scrutinised advertising environment. The 10-year media contract that accompanied it demonstrates the long-term commercial value the market places on this inventory type. DigiSite's model is built on the same regulatory framework, applied systematically across the UK's most commercially active construction corridors.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="text-center">
          <span class="font-mono font-semibold text-amber leading-none" style="font-size: 80px;" data-counter data-target="10">0</span>
          <p class="font-mono font-semibold text-[13px] uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-mid-grey mt-2">YEAR MEDIA CONTRACT</p>
          <p class="font-mono text-[11px] text-mid-grey/60 mt-3">Oxford Street, 2024</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Closing statement -->
    <div class="reveal text-center py-10 md:py-20">
      <p class="font-grotesk font-bold text-off-white mx-auto" style="font-size: clamp(20px, 3vw, 26px); letter-spacing: -0.01em; max-width: 720px;">
        The market exists. The technology is proven. The planning pathway is established. The inventory category is empty.
      </p>
    </div>

  </div>
</section>
